==English==
===Etymology===
20th century United States urban African American and Mexican American slang.  Origin uncertain.  Possibly derived from Spanish "hombre", or American English term "hometown boy".

===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]] US [ˈhoʊm.bɔɪ]

===Noun===
'''homeboy'''
#Someone, particularly a male acquaintance, from one's hometown.
#A close friend or fellow member of a youth gang.
#An inner-city youth.

===Derived terms===
* [[homey]]

